05/11/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Zoran Konjanovski reaffirmed on Thursday (November 4th) that membership in NATO remains Macedonia's top priority. 
Opening a meeting of chiefs of staff of the Adriatic Charter member states, he stressed the need for implementing reforms necessary to the NATO accession process. 
US Ambassador Philip Reeker praised Macedonia's contribution to peacekeeping operations abroad. 
He said that Macedonian-US partnership is successful and will continue. 
At the end of the meeting, the participants adopted a joint statement pledging to strengthen relations in the region as part of efforts to maintain permanent peace and stability. 
The Adriatic Charter members are Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia and Montenegro. 
(A1, Radio Free Europe, MIA, Sitel - 04/11/10)
